Quote:  inihina - Hinahina or Mahoe, in Maori - was considered the best wood for the rubber [in firemaking]; but Karamu, Karaka, Ake, Rautini, and Kokopere (Maori, Kawakawa) were used as the <i>Kahunaki</i>, or grooved piece of wood.
